@litterypaws @SBF_FTX Even under strict guidelines you have a lot of options:

- Excluding the irrelevent data while keeping what is essential
- What's the best visualisation to clearly convey as much as possible?
- What story should lead up to the presented data?

All of those play an important role

@abecadariun @SBF_FTX Any dataset can be used to create an infinite amount of datasets and visualisations. Only a very select few of those are important.

The hardest is selecting the fewest possible in order to convey as much info as possible in a clear and concise manner.
RT @SBF_FTX: 1) People suck at presenting results form a scientific study.

@SBF_FTX Producing data is easy. The hard part is:
- Producing the right data
- Presenting it in the clearest and most concise way possible
- Trying to cover all aspects of what you're studying and not having your data induce a bias

Only the very best data scientists master those ğŸ‘‘
